sources.title: Public Enemy #4 (1955) TRUE CRIME
sources.description:
It's FRIDAY@PizzaFLIX 
Stars: Myron Healey, Don C. Harvey, Frank Gerstle
Director: Bill Karn

This True Crime exposé goes deep into the criminal mind of John Omar Pinson, the three-time loser once listed on the FBI’s Top Ten Most Wanted list. He’s portrayed by veteran small-screen baddie Myron Healey, and his twisted tale of murder & mayhem is based entirely on intel from law enforcement agencies across the five western states.
